title: Printer's Sample Book (USA), 1866–70
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs to be used for printing textiles. Contains 56 samples of printed fabric, mostly florals.

tombstone.epitaph: Printer's Sample Book (USA), 1866–70; Manufactured by Old Pacific Print Works ; paper and cotton; Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts; 1945-55-29
